b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe07039.htm)  [Next](sbe07041.htm)\n\n* * *\n\np. 138\n\n# XXXVIII.\n\n1\\. Causing (bodily) pain to a Brahma _n_ a;\n\n2\\. Smelling at things which ought not to be smelt (such as excrements), or at\nspirituous liquor;\n\n3\\. Dishonest dealing;\n\n4\\. Sexual connection with cattle;\n\n5\\. And (sexual connection) with a man (or unnatural intercourse with a\nwoman):\n\n6\\. Such are the crimes effecting loss of caste.\n\n7\\. He who has knowingly committed one of the acts effecting loss of caste\nshall perform the Santapana[1] penance; he who has done so unawares shall\nperform the Pra _g_ apatya[1] penance.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: XXXIX.](sbe07041.htm)\n\n'